parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cracked Clutch Cylinder Well in Transmission
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked clutch cylinder well in the transmission can cause the "Service Vehicle" warning indicator to illuminate, leading to transmission failure, which can result in loss of vehicle control, accidents, or strand the driver.

The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become heavy, stiff, and difficult to turn, making it challenging to control the vehicle, potentially leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel is hard to turn
the steering wheel does not return easily to center
the steering wheel requires manual assistance to return to center
the vehicle tracks side to side on uneven or grooved payment surfaces
the vehicle is pushed to the right or left when a larger vehicle passes on the freeway.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydro boost unit can cause a loss of hydraulic fluid, leading to a failure of the power steering and power braking systems, which can result in a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
The malfunction of the anti-theft system can cause the vehicle to not start, leaving the driver stranded, and potentially causing inconvenience or even safety risks in certain situations.
symptoms: the dashboard displays an error message
lost communication with the vehicle's computer system.
